components: FUEL SYSTEM, DIESEL,ELECTRICAL SYSTEM,EXTERIOR LIGHTING,VISIBILITY,STRUCTURE,INTERIOR LIGHTING,EQUIPMENT
summary: WHEN THE VEHICLE HAD 45 GALLONS OF FUEL OR LESS AND MADE A RIGHT HAND TURN THE VEHICLE STALLED.  BY THE  CONSUMER PULLED OVER THE RV STARTED BACK UP.  THE PAINT ON THE DRIVERS SIDE BLISTERED AND THE PAINT ON HE PASSENGER SIDE HAD SWIRL MARKS.  THE OUTSIDE DOOR HANDLE FELL OFF.  THE WINDSHIELD WAS REPLACE.  BOTH KEYLESS REMOTES WERE INOPERATIVE.  THE BRAKE LIGHT ON THE DRIVERS SIDE WENT OUT.  THE CHASSIS BATTERY WENT DEAD IN LESS THAN TEN DAYS.  THE LIGHT FIXTURE COLLECTED WATER INSIDE WHICH DRIPPED INSIDE THE RV.  THE KITCHEN SLIDE WAS CROOKED WHICH RESULTED IN WIND NOISE INSIDE THE RV.    *NLM   *NLM
